content: DO NOT BUY FOR ROTORCRAFT. Many of the test prep questions for rotorcraft are gyroplane and fixed wing. Waste of money for ROTORCRAFT students. Will not give you an accurate questionnaire for helicopter students. Waste of money.
This app need autosave asap !!
Useful for rotorcraft knowledge test prep, would be nice if there was an option to bookmark questions for future reference.
Great Tool.

Lets start by saying having an app is a great tool to prepare for your written, any help is worth reaching for. That said, ASA is not known for being the top choice, HOWEVER, it was priced comfortably and the interface is clean. I would love to feedback in full but google won't let me type that much...
Great learning experience

Been studying with this app for my knowledge test, i take it this week. It does a great job explaining and referencing the correct answers and I like that i can study on the go. Only thing I find frustrating is I cant look back at previous tests to see what areas I struggle. I'd like a better way to track progress. Good app, thanks
Excellent software. I used it to study and acted the test!

May 2020: The app is great but needs a big update. I studied & passed but scored much lower than expected. The Qs in the app didn't cover any of the new Qs. Incld the ACS stds when studying bcuz the FAA is aligning the written test with those stds. More new questions coming in June 2020!
Do not waste your time and your money please,this app is trash trust me.
Very nice app.very helpfully
Perfect for studdying. I found it very useful and accurate.
These prepware apps have worked great for my private and instrument helicopter written.
best

Good for multiple choice and basic learning but all of the figure questions are horribly wrong. Ex. Aircraft departs at 0845 CST 2 hour flight to MST A. 1345Z B. 1445Z C. 1645Z How is the answer not 1545Z
I wish it was updated for 2019
please update to the latest questions!

An excellent application which is helping me a lot for the FFA Exam. However, sometimes when I press the next button, it moves me 2 more questions while I only pressed the next button once. Same case on previous button. Fix that Please and I will give it 5 stars

I'm very unhappy with this purchase. I've completed the Private Pilot, Rotocraft numerous times as well as the Recreational Pilot, Rotocraft and more than half the questions relate to airplanes only. Is this functioning correctly?
Frequently crashes or loses your progress, with 160 question long tests it can be quite frustrating

Used this app to get a 100% on my written. There are areas to be improved like more flexible and rich progress keeping or highlighting questions for reviewing but I was able to supplement it with external notes.
It's fine. Works for the purpose. You can't leave the app for more than, say, ten minutes or it'll crash when you try to go back. I'd expect more out of a ten dollar app.
Pass my written with 92. Helped me a lot.
Very useful. Passed with 93%

Becon light military airport become flashes white and green is AIM 2-1-10 
and not AIM 2-1-9. THERE IS NO easy way to inform of a mistype.
Doesn't save progress; even if you select "save and exit," you have to start anew the next time.
I passed my written exam with a 83% two üëç‚òù
During the study sessions A lot of the maps have no legends so you have no way to find the answer. Otherwise a decent app.

This is the worst application I have encounterred. It's like Study Island, only worse. It frequently marks correct answers as incorrect, asks irrelevant questions (though the FAA may be responsible for that), has unhelpful explanations, no longer tells me whether my answers are right or wrong & lt costs money. Even for a free application, lt would be terrible. Payment is just the icing on the hair cake.
Questions span the breadth of knowledge requirements. Wish it kept track during study mode.

The app crashes when anything else pops up on my phone and takes my attention away from studying. I have yet to be able to finish a practice test. How much did I pay for this app? How is this acceptable?
Got an 83% on my written, thanks asa!
Passed my Written exam with an 88, thanks asa!
Loses all progress unless you manually save, leaving the app and coming back causes it to crash. Very poor and basic coding.
This a great app
The app offers a save feature so you can come back to where you left off, but it's not worth having because the app crashes and loses my spot every other time I use it.

The figures seem to be outdated from the older test guided. I currently have the 2016 one so they don't match up. Also I get tested on certain questions that were removed from the Private Pilot Knowledge test.

I am constantly changing to different apps and it starts over or loses my progress.  Insanely annoying,  even for just that one time you need to leave the app for a message and you are deep into a long test section.

Great little app, but with two improvements it could be better: 1) if there was a mode showing only correct answers and 2) if the app would remember where you left off after closing in question sequence.  Other than that, this app is great and will help you towards your private pilot written exam!
How can I obtain my scores at the end of test mode?
Sometimes when I switch between apps and come back to the test later, it starts everything over which is very annoying. Some glider tests are not relevant to glider.
Passed with an 88%!!
Works great
I never got told which questions were right and which were wrong
I got 100% for my MET exam.
Unfortunately, private pilot has stopped working.
Helped me a lot. Got 95. Easy to use.  Worked very well with my Samsung Galaxy Note 3. Clear graphics, and not a battery eating app. I  definitely recommend it for Private Pilot test.
Awesome
Helped me get a 92
Thanks for the last update!

I actually spoke with the Techs about the change from the black background to the white background. I was told that it will not change anytime soon.   It is really hard to read the answers on a white background and makes studying very difficult. Significant train on the eyes.
It help me pass the test
There is no way to grade my test! I want a refund! The iPad version is better for the same price.

This has been extremely helpful while studying for the written exam. I'm able to study whenever I have free time, and I love that it gives explanations for the answers. However, I've noticed in test mode that some of the figures either have out of date maps, or new maps with out of date questions. They'll refer to something that's not there. Would be five stars if they fixed these
How do you submit your test when you are done? The next icon goes off so u can't click it

It is aggravating to complete a test  and it not grade it. Have done several tests and have yet for it to grade one. Not worth the money if functions don't work. Fix this and it will be worth the money.
Will not work on s4
Great for any pilot really, it's great for student pilots. It is also a good aid for current pilots just to keep refreshing on certain topics.

I loved using this app but it recently stopped working on my Samsung S4.  Unfortunately, I need to take my ground exam in the next few weeks and now have to purchase another app to practice.  I am sure the developers will fix this eventually.  I wouldn't purchase this app until this issue is fixed unless you can test it on your phone first.

I have used this to study. About a week ago it stopped working(keeps crashing) on my phone (note 3). I have deleted and reinstalled it several times. Also waited maybe it was a bad update. Still nothing. Would give 5 stars if it worked again for me.
Also didn't allow a refund on the play store after only a few minutes of use.  Not nice.
This is a great study tool. If I have some spare time, I can take a sample test.
Cleared my Private Pilot written exam with the score of 95%. Thank you Prepware ! P.S very handy!

The app is alright for self study, but a few of the referenced figures do not match the questions. Also there seems to be no way to aggregate questions you've missed into a single "flash card" set. A bit disappointing.
Extremely useful for either long study sessions or a quick quiz with down time. I use to as a refresher after getting my license.
Crashes a lot of my galaxy s3
The new update took away the ability to view the figures. I just uninstalled then reinstalled and now it works fine again!
New update made it so I can't see images to reference for questions. Please fix problem.
Awesome and helps me a lot.
My wish list is a glossary of terms. There were words I had to lookup. Be nice to do it right here in the program.
Even after having passed my written test the first try, I still brush up on my knowledge from time to time with this awesome app. I highly recommend this priceless study tool.
I passed my written test!!! thanks to prepware.
I use at every odd moment to prepare for my private certificate test. Very handy.
Excelent
Not much substance other than test questions. Would be cool to have interactive course instruction.
Great tool if used properly, memorize and good luck on your FAA Ground test :)
Just questions with basic explanation of the answer. Not the same subject layout or questions as in my JAR JAA workbooks. Wish I could get my money back.
Great app exactly what I was looking for! Helped me pass my test!

I'm in a pilot development program and have found this to be on par with questions from the jeppesen books. Also instructors have reccomended this asa app. I do too for an advantage on your test and general knowledge.
This application sucks the test bank of questions is small and it does not save your practice test results for reviewing the ones you missed at a later time

I recently purchased each prepware program for Private, Instrument, and Commercial. While they are all extremely useful for studying away from home/office, the software is unstable and unreliable (quite the opposite of the ideal aircraft actually). If I minimize the program for a moment to answer a call, view a text message, or use the calculator, it is more than likely that the prepware will either crash or send me back to the home screen. Forget about being able to finish a test.

I used this app to study for the written, passed with 85%. ASA Prepware supplied my letter of endorsement after paying $14.95 for 5 practice tests on their website and passing 2 with 80% or better. After passing the FAA written I sent my test results to ASA and they mailed me a nice certificate which I put in a frame.
Great app for an on-the-go study aid.  Perfect for a quick few min or for a few hours.  Im sure this app is will help me pass my test(s)!
Perfect app! Helped me get a 92!!!

The app is really exactly what I expected.  It could be better -- for example, if it saved your study progress.  Also the charts can be very hard to view on a Samsung Galaxy Nexus, but that's the nature of air charts.  This kind of study app is a great thing to have when learning the ropes for your next certificate.  Well worth $10.
I go to a part 141 school and this app was my best friend. The best 10$ I've ever spent for flight training. Passed my FAA written with a 90%!
Well worth the money. Just wish it would save your spot after you stop studying so you don't have to skip through.
Now I am studying for my FAA written test whenever I have a few minutes free.
All's well
This is the only source that truly helps passing the private written. I just passed it. The test has 62 questions, copied & pasted from this app.
Great app, helped me study and pass my test without carrying figure books around everywhere with me
Works really well. The questions have great explanations with them, and the images are really clear and can be zoomed in. Much better than websites.
You can study anywhere! App works GREAT. Must buy.
Excellent tool for prep. Has all questions with explanations. Test mode and study mode. Highly recommend it.
